-- Australia shares seen bouncing from 2-1/2 month lows 
-- 
-- Tue Jul 01, 2014 07:22PM EDT
-- None



SYDNEY, July 2 (Reuters) - Australian shares are set to rebound from a 2-1/2 month low in early trade on Wednesday, buoyed by record highs on Wall Street overnight, while investors will keep an eye on local trade balance data due later.

* Local share price index futures <YAPcm1> rose 0.4 percent to 5,360, a 15.9-point discount to the underlying S&P/ASX 200 index <.AXJO> close. The benchmark fell 0.4 percent on Tuesday.  * New Zealand's benchmark NZX 50 index <.NZ50> added 0.1 percent in early trade. * The Dow and the S&P 500 closed at record highs overnight as manufacturing activity picked up in the United States and Asia and increased optimism about the global economy's health.  * Copper pulled back from its strongest levels in nearly four months, while benchmark 62 percent grade iron ore <.IO62-CNI=SI> rose slightly to $94.20 a tonne.  * Gold reversed early gains as investors took profits after strong exchange-traded fund buying sent prices to a near two-month peak earlier.  * Australasian food company Goodman Fielder Ltd <GFF.NZ> <GFF.AX> said it would recommend shareholders accept a reduced takeover offer from Wilmar International Ltd <WLIL.SI> and Hong Kong investor First Pacific Co <0142.HK>, valuing the company at A$1.32 billion ($1.25 billion). [ID:nL4N0PC4V4] * Singapore's Frasers Centrepoint Ltd <FRCT.SI> has reached a deal to buy Australia's Australand Property Group <ALZ.AX> for about A$2.6 billion. [ID:nL4N0PC4P9] * New Horizon Coal Ltd <NHO.AX> says it has commenced a strategic review in releation to its investment in the Kinney Coal Project. [ID:nWNBS00HZ5] * Archer Exploration Ltd <AXE.AX> said an action lodged by Magnesium Developments has been discontinued that affected part of Archer's Leigh Creek Magnesite Project. [ID:nWNBS00HZ7] * Monthly trade balance data from the Reserve Bank of Australia is due out later on Wednesday.   ----------------------MARKET SNAPSHOT @ 2302 GMT ------------ INSTRUMENT   LAST   PCT CHG   NET CHG S&P 500 <.SPX>   1973.32  0.67%13.090 USD/JPY <JPY=>   101.54  -0.01%-0.010 10-YR US TSY YLD<US10YT=RR>  2.5665  --  #N/A SPOT GOLD   <XAU=>   1326.1   0.05% 0.660 US CRUDE<CLc1>   105.27  -0.07%-0.070 DOW JONES   <.DJI>   16956.07 0.77%129.47 ASIA ADRS   <.B